<topic id="dita-table-properties">
  <title>Editing Table Properties in DITA</title>
  <body>
    <p>To customize the look of a table, place the cursor anywhere in a table and invoke the
          <uicontrol><image href="../img/TableProperties16.png"/>Table Properties (<shortcut
          conkeyref="reusable_oxygen_shortcuts_list/ctrl_t_shortcut"/>)</uicontrol> action from the
        <uicontrol>Table</uicontrol> submenu of the contextual menu or <uicontrol>DITA</uicontrol>
        menu<ph product="author editor"> (or from the toolbar)</ph>.</p>
    <p conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/table-properties-notes"/>
    <p conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/cals-table-props"/>
    <p>For a <uicontrol>Simple</uicontrol> table, you can customize the following:<ul
        id="ul_njq_lsw_zn">
        <li><uicontrol>Table</uicontrol> - The frame attribute.</li>
        <li><uicontrol>Row</uicontrol> - The row type.</li>
      </ul></p>
  </body>
</topic>
